  "notes": [
    "All transfer applicants must meet the University of California admissions eligibility requirements and the campus’s admission selection criteria. All requirements must be completed by the end of the spring term prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility and admission to UC Santa Cruz, visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that guarantees your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
    "THIS IS A SCREENING MAJOR. Screening majors require completion of specific preparatory coursework and/or a minimum GPA. For details on the specific screening requirements for this major, refer to the \" Transfer Admission Screening Policy \" below. Additional coursework listed under \"Recommended Preparation\" is not required for admission but is strongly recommended to support timely degree completion. For more information, including a list of screening majors and non-screening majors , visit the UCSC Admissions website.",
    "Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level (IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the Degree Progress Unit website .",
    "This major is intended for students who are interested in teaching science in high schools in the state of California. Science Education B.S. Transfer Admission Screening Policy Transfer students must complete a minimum of six of the following courses, or their articulated equivalents, with a grade of C (2.0) or better by the end of the spring term prior to transferring in the fall: BIOE 20B: Development and Physiology BIOE 20C: Ecology and Evolution BIOL 20A: Cell and Molecular Biology MATH 11A: Calculus with Applications MATH 11B: Calculus with Applications PHYS 6A: Introductory Physics I PHYS 6B: Introductory Physics II PHYS 6C: Introductory Physics III STAT 5: Statistics CHEM 3A: General Chemistry* CHEM 3B: General Chemistry* CHEM 3C: General Chemistry* CHEM 4A: Advanced General Chemistry: Molecular Structure and Reactivity* CHEM 4B: Advanced General Chemistry: Molecular Structure and Reactivity* *Courses from either the CHEM 3 series or the CHEM 4 series, not both, may be used. It is strongly recommended that community college students complete all General Chemistry coursework for their intended major at one institution prior to transfer to UC Santa Cruz. Strongly Recommended Major Preparation In addition to the six courses required for admission, students are strongly recommended to complete three additional courses from the above course list prior to transfer to ensure timely graduation. Additional Information for Transfer Prospective students are encouraged to prioritize required and recommended major preparation, and may additionally complete courses that articulate to UC Santa Cruz general education requirements as time allows. Please visit the Physics Department website to learn more about this major. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Science Education B.S. Program Statement"
  ]
